The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Colleagues bullet hits constable

 Calcutta, Feb. 25: Gautam Dutta Gupta, a constable of Garden Reach police station, was seriously injured after being hit by a stray bullet from the service revolver of his colleague, says a staff reporter.

 The incident took place when the two were about to start work around 9.50 this morning. Police said Animesh Singh had forgotten to lock his trigger while loading his revolver ? an offence that could invite stern disciplinary action.

 Dutta Gupta, 45, was admitted to hospital. Singh has been asked to give an explanation in writing to the police top brass. 




